  ],
  "remarks": "Sergey Lagodiuk is Deputy Chief of the General Staff of the Armed Forces of the Republic of Belarus and Head of the Main Operational Directorate. The Main Operational Directorate participates in military policy of the Republic of Belarus and acts as the leading structural unit of the General Staff in the system of strategic planning and management. In his position, Sergey Lagodiuk oversees the actions of the Main Operational Directorate. In addition, Sergey Lagodiuk is a member of the Joint Board of the Ministry of Defence of the Republic of Belarus and the Russian Federation and therefore participates in the bilateral Russian-Belarusian cooperation in the military sphere. The Republic of Belarus is used as a military hub of the Russian military and that strategically puts pressure on Ukraine to keep troops near the border, thus weakening defensive capabilities of Ukraine. Therefore, Sergey Lagodiuk, as a member of the Joint Board of the Ministry of Defence of the Republic of Belarus and the Russian Federation, is supporting materially the Government of the Russian Federation, which is responsible for the annexation of Crimea and the destabilisation of Ukraine.",
